%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnconfuse%20Me%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGates%2C%20whose%20father%20died%20in%202020%20after%20suffering%20from%20Alzheimer's%20disease%2C%20said%20he%20used%20to%20compete%20to%20sleep%20less%20with%20other%20colleagues%20at%20Microsoft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIn%20my%20thirties%20and%20forties%20when%20there%20would%20be%20a%20conversation%20about%20sleep%2C%20it%20would%20be%20like%3A%20'Oh%20I%20only%20sleep%20six%20hours%2C%20and%20the%20other%20guys%20like%3A%20'No%20I%20only%20sleep%20five'%20and%20'Well%20sometimes%20I%20don't%20sleep%20at%20all%2C'%20and%20I'd%20be%20like%3A%20'Wow%20those%20guys%20are%20so%20good.%20I%20have%20to%20try%20harder%20because%20sleep%20is%20laziness%20and%20unnecessary.'%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire%20has%20changed%20his%20tune%20about%20sleep%20since%20then%20and%20started%20tracking%20his%20daily%20%26quot%3Bsleep%20score%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20A%20sleep%20score%20is%20determined%20by%20the%20length%20and%20quality%20of%20your%20sleep%20and%20is%20something%20that%20can%20be%20tracked%20on%20an%20Apple%20Watch%20or%20a%20Fitbit%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20what%20we%20know%20is%20that%20to%20maintain%20brain%20health%2C%20getting%20good%20sleep%20even%20back%20to%20teen%20years%20is%20super%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Gates%20said.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20most%20predictive%20factors%20of%20any%20dementia%2C%20including%20Alzheimer's%2C%20is%20whether%20you're%20getting%20good%20sleep%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERogan%20chimed%20in%20on%20the%20conversation%20by%20comparing%20attitudes%20to%20sleeping%20with%20smoking%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20young%20the%20convention%20was%20'you'll%20sleep%20when%20you're%20dead.'%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20used%20to%20think%20smoking%20is%20healthy.%20It%20is%20similar.%20That's%20where%20we%20are%20culturally%20%E2%80%93%20the%20things%20people%20think%20and%20understand%20about%20their%20own%20brains%20are%20where%20they%20were%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s.%20It's%20so%20far%20off%20from%20what%20actual%20science%20is%20reflective%20of.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGates%20has%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-book-recommendation-why-we-sleep-matthew-walker-2019-12%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3Etaken%20tips%20from%20a%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20%26quot%3BWhy%20We%20Sleep%26quot%3B%20by%20neuroscientist%20and%20sleep%20expert%20Matthew%20Walker%2C%20which%20he%20reviewed%20in%20his%20blog%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gatesnotes.com%2FWhy-We-Sleep%3FWT.mc_id%3D12_10_2019_08_EOYBooks2019_MED-media_%26WT.tsrc%3DMEDmedia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGates%20Notes%26quot%3B%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20routinely%20pulled%20all-nighters%20when%20we%20had%20to%20deliver%20a%20piece%20of%20software%2C%26quot%3B%20Gates%20wrote%20in%20the%20review.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20or%20twice%2C%20I%20stayed%20up%20two%20nights%20in%20a%20row.%20I%20knew%20I%20wasn't%20as%20sharp%20when%20I%20was%20operating%20mostly%20on%20caffeine%20and%20adrenaline%2C%20but%20I%20was%20obsessed%20with%20my%20work%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20that%20sleeping%20a%20lot%20was%20lazy.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire%20now%20aims%20to%20get%20between%20seven%20and%20eight%20hours%20of%20sleep%20a%20night.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-microsoft-used-to-think-sleep-was-lazy-unnecessary-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691403873000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d0a8d220f1cf0019cbb506%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bu