%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20the%20US%20wants%20to%20build%20more%20homes%2C%20slow%20down%20rent%20growth%2C%20and%20give%20more%20people%20a%20place%20to%20live%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20learn%20from%20New%20Zealand.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20a%20bustling%20neighborhood%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20single-family%20homes%2C%20triplexes%2C%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20businesses%2C%20and%20public%20amenities.%20Rent%20growth%20is%20slow%2C%20home%20prices%20are%20reasonable%2C%20and%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20affordable-housing%20options.%20Families%2C%20young%20people%2C%20retired%20folks%2C%20and%20businesses%20are%20all%20able%20to%20coexist%2C%20making%20the%20area%20diverse%20and%20vibrant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20most%20American%20neighborhoods%20don't%20look%20like%20this.%20Instead%2C%20huge%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20have%20zoning%20laws%20that%20make%20it%20illegal%20to%20build%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2019%2F06%2F18%2Fupshot%2Fcities-across-america-question-single-family-zoning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanything%20other%20than%20a%20single-unit%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20these%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20originally%20designed%20to%20keep%20residential%20neighborhoods%20separate%20from%20manufacturing%20and%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.fivethirtyeight.com%2Fredlining%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esegregate%20and%20exclude%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20based%20on%20race%20%E2%80%94%20are%20running%20up%20against%20a%20harsh%20reality.%20American%20cities%2C%20especially%20those%20with%20growing%20job%20markets%20and%20a%20healthy%20influx%20of%20new%20residents%2C%20need%20to%20build%20millions%20of%20new%20homes%20to%20keep%20housing%20from%20becoming%20unaffordable.%20And%20keeping%20single-family-only%20zoning%20laws%20in%20place%20makes%20it%20almost%20impossible%20to%20meet%20these%20areas'%20housing%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20housing%20more%20abundant%20and%20affordable%2C%20economists%20and%20urban%20planners%20say%2C%20we%20need%20to%20upzone%20many%20neighborhoods%20%E2%80%94%20legalize%20the%20construction%20of%20denser%2C%20taller%20housing%20like%20duplexes%2C%20triplexes%2C%20and%20townhomes.%20Upzoning%20won't%20cause%20the%20price%20of%20existing%20housing%20to%20suddenly%20tumble%2C%20but%20it%20will%20slow%20the%20growth%20of%20housing%20costs%20by%20meeting%20demand.%20It's%20a%20necessary%2C%20but%20not%20sufficient%20first%20step%20in%20solving%20the%20affordability%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20enormous%20amount%20of%20economics%20literature%20going%20back%20decades%20that%20shows%20us%20that%20places%20that%20have%20restrictive%20zoning%20build%20less%20housing%20over%20time%2C%20and%20that%20making%20zoning%20more%20restrictive%20reduces%20supply%20and%20increases%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Jenny%20Schuetz%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20urban%20economics%20and%20housing%20policy%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institute%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20essentially%20a%20unanimous%20consensus%20among%20economists%20and%20policy%20analysts%20that%20this%20is%20the%20direction%20we%20have%20to%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAggressive%20opposition%20to%20zoning%20reform%20has%20limited%20the%20number%20of%20real-world%20models%20we%20have%20in%20the%20US.%20So%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fnew-zealands-bipartisan-housing-reforms-offer-a-model-to-other-countries%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperts%20have%20looked%20abroad%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20solutions.%20New%20Zealand%20stands%20out%20as%20an%20exceptional%20example%20of%20how%20to%20successfully%20boost%20housing%20supply%20through%20zoning%20reform.%20Facing%20an%20urgent%20housing%20crisis%2C%20the%20island%20nation%20implemented%20upzoning%20measures%20that%20legalized%20the%20building%20of%20medium-density%20housing.%20Not%20only%20did%20this%20help%20to%20slow%20down%20skyrocketing%20housing%20costs%2C%20it%20inspired%20a%20bipartisan%2C%20nationwide%20expansion%20of%20the%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Auckland%20example%20is%20so%20particularly%20groundbreaking%20because%20it's%20no%20longer%20a%20theoretical%20debate%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Maltman%2C%20an%20Australian%20economist%20who's%20closely%20studied%20New%20Zealand's%20housing%20reforms%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20makes%20it%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20sell%20to%20people.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Kiwi%20model%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Zealand%20has%20long%20had%20the%20same%20issue%20facing%20many%20American%20cities%3A%20very%20low-density%20residential%20neighborhoods%20that%20restricted%20the%20amount%20of%20housing%20that%20could%20be%20built.%20In%20the%201970s%20and%20'80s%2C%20the%20country%20even%20%26quot%3Bdownzoned%26quot%3B%20residential%20areas%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tewaihanga.govt.nz%2Fassets%2FUploads%2FThe-decline-of-housing-supply-in-New-Zealand.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurther%20limiting%20housing%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20much%20of%20the%20country.%20As%20its%20population%20grew%20rapidly%20%E2%80%94%20expanding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fnew-zealands-bipartisan-housing-reforms-offer-a-model-to-other-countries%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealmost%2011%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%202013%20and%202018%20%E2%80%94%20a%20serious%20housing-affordability%20crisis%20started%20brewing.%20Home%20prices%20in%20Auckland%2C%20New%20Zealand's%20biggest%20city%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lewis.ucla.edu%2F2023%2F03%2F08%2F45-what-happened-when-auckland-upzoned-everywhere-with-ryan-greenaway-mcgrevy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoubled%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%202009%20and%202016%20and%20prices%20across%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.qv.co.nz%2Fprice-index%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efollowed%20close%20behind%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20even%20began%20to%20pay%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20a%20month%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2016%2Fsep%2F07%2Fwhy-auckland-is-leading-the-worlds-housing-market-boom%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20rent%20garages%20in%20Auckland%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20bathrooms%20or%20kitchens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20face%20of%20this%20growing%20problem%2C%20the%20city%20decided%20to%20act.%20A%20law%20passed%20in%202016%20allowed%20for%20%26quot%3Bgentle%20density%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20making%20it%20legal%20to%20build%20duplexes%2C%20triplexes%2C%20and%20townhomes%20on%20single-home%20lots.%20The%20policy%20tripled%20the%20city's%20housing%20capacity.%20Between%202015%20and%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.auckland.ac.nz%2Fassets%2Fbusiness%2Fabout%2Four-research%2Fresearch-institutes-and-centres%2FCARE%2FThe%2520Impact%2520of%2520Upzoning%2520on%2520Housing%2520Construction%2520in%2520Auckland.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20new%20housing%20units%20permitted%20in%20the%20city%20grew%20from%206%2C000%20to%20more%20than%2014%2C300.%20Auckland%20went%20from%20mostly%20single-family%20homes%20to%20a%20much%20denser%20mix%20of%20multiunit%20homes%20and%20attached%20single-unit%20buildings.%20In%20a%202021%20research%20paper%2C%20Ryan%20Greenaway-McGrevy%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Center%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Auckland%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.auckland.ac.nz%2Fassets%2Fbusiness%2Fabout%2Four-research%2Fresearch-institutes-and-centres%2FCARE%2FThe%2520Impact%2520of%2520Upzoning%2520on%2520Housing%2520Construction%2520in%2520Auckland%2520v2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Auckland's%20policy%20succeeded%20in%20its%20twin%20goals%20of%20boosting%20supply%20and%20increasing%20density.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20per%20capita%20terms%2C%20Auckland%20has%20gone%20from%20somewhat%20of%20a%20laggard%20to%20a%20leader%20among%20New%20Zealand's%20largest%20cities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20in%20an%20email%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20number%20of%20per%20capita%20construction%20permits%20issued%20in%20the%20city%20hit%20a%20%26quot%3Brecord%20high%20in%202020%20or%20so%2C%20which%20was%20surpassed%20in%202021%20and%20again%20in%202022.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20taken%20on%20Dec.%2011%2C%202020%20shows%20houses%20in%20suburbs%20of%20Wellington%2C%20New%20Zealand.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cd2eb2f5d4870019e1cc1f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20Zealand%20traditionally%20had%20low-density%20residential%20neighborhoods%20dominated%20by%20detached%20single-family%20homes%20until%20it%20passed%20new%20laws%20to%20allow%20more%20homes.%3Cp%3EGuo%20Lei%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20not%20only%20led%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20new%20housing%2C%20it%20also%20slowed%20the%20pace%20of%20rising%20housing%20costs.%20Maltman%20found%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20reversal%20of%20the%20trend%26quot%3B%20of%20skyrocketing%20costs%20in%20Auckland.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20significant%20slowing%20of%20rental%20price%20growth%20since%20the%20policy%20was%20implemented%2C%26quot%3B%20Maltman%20told%20me%2C%20referring%20to%20the%202016%20reforms.%20%26quot%3BBoth%20incomes%20and%20inflation%20have%20grown%20faster%20than%20the%20price%20of%20rental%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20voices%20of%20New%20Zealand%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stuff.co.nz%2Fbusiness%2Fproperty%2F89352761%2Fhigh-court-rules-in-favour-of-unitary-plan-decision-process%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomeowners%20who%20opposed%20dense%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20loud%20in%20the%20rollout%20of%20the%20policy%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fd39d3mj7qio96p.cloudfront.net%2Fmedia%2Fdocuments%2FER57_Community_acceptance_of_MDH_development.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202020%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Auckland%20residents%20were%20increasingly%20supportive%20of%20new%20construction%20in%20their%20neighborhoods%20%E2%80%94%2064%25%20supported%20medium-density%20housing%20as%20a%20way%20to%20solve%20the%20city's%20housing%20shortage.%20The%20success%20of%20Auckland's%20upzoning%20even%20helped%20inspire%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rnz.co.nz%2Fnews%2Fpolitical%2F453824%2Fhousing-density-to-increase-across-new-zealand-under-rare-bipartisan-solution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebipartisan%20national%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20passed%20in%202021%2C%20that%20requires%20the%20country's%20biggest%20cities%20to%20allow%20medium-density%20building%20in%20residential%20areas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20hasn't%20been%20a%20silver%20bullet%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand%20continues%20to%20face%20housing%20challenges.%20The%202021%20policy%20has%20faced%20significant%20local%20pushback%20and%20the%20center-right%20National%20Party%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rnz.co.nz%2Fnews%2Fpolitical%2F490589%2Fnational-signals-backdown-on-bipartisan-housing-policy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturned%20against%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20pandemic%20and%20seesawing%20interest%20rates%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F06%2F19%2Fbusiness%2Fnew-zealand-housing-prices.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewreaked%20havoc%20on%20the%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20country%20is%20now%20technically%20in%20a%20recession.%20But%20experts%20say%20things%20would%20be%20much%20worse%20without%20the%20zoning%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEarly%20struggles%20and%20successes%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20there%20are%20many%20opponents%20to%20zoning%20reform%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0particularly%20higher-income%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2022%2F04%2Flocal-government-community-input-housing-public-transportation%2F629625%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20homeowners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20their%20neighborhoods%20change.%20Some%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fideas%2Farchive%2F2022%2F11%2Fus-housing-supply-shortage-crisis-2022%2F672240%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equestion%20the%20basic%20laws%20of%20supply%20and%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20insist%20that%20new%20housing%20actually%20raises%20prices.%20Others%20have%20more%20founded%20concerns%20about%20strains%20on%20infrastructure%2C%20schools%2C%20and%20other%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20cities%20are%20also%20operating%20under%20old%2C%20complex%20regimes%20of%20regulations%20that%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20build.%20Land-use%20regulations%20tend%20to%20pile%20up%20and%20sometimes%20contradict%20each%20other%2C%20Vicki%20Been%2C%20who%20served%20as%20New%20York%20City's%20deputy%20mayor%20of%20Housing%20and%20Economic%20Development%20under%20Mayor%20Bill%20de%20Blasio%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you%20have%20to%2C%20really%2C%20every%20once%20in%20a%20while%2C%20just%20sort%20of%20take%20a%20scalpel%20and%20say%2C%20'OK%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20update%20this%2C%20we're%20gonna%20cut%20through%20all%20of%20the%20layers%20of%20complexity%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20New%20Zealand%20offers%20a%20way%20out%20of%20this%20morass.%20The%20country%C2%A0is%20a%20particularly%20good%20model%20for%20the%20US%2C%20because%20the%20countries%20have%20relatively%20similar%20urban-planning%20systems%2C%20land-use%20regimes%2C%20and%20geographies%2C%20Schuetz%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20similar%20to%20the%20US%20than%2C%20say%2C%20much%20of%20Europe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENolan%20Gray%2C%20a%20city%20planner%20and%20research%20director%20for%20California%20YIMBY%2C%20agreed.%20%26quot%3BA%20typical%20New%20Zealand%20city%20looks%20a%20lot%20like%20a%20typical%20US%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20said.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20construction%20happened%20in%20the%20age%20of%20the%20car%3B%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20single-family%20neighborhoods%3B%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20low-rise%20commercial%20corridors.%26quot%3B%20Like%20Americans%2C%20average%20New%20Zealanders%20also%20treat%20their%20homes%20as%20an%20investment%20%26quot%3Bthat%20they%20secretly%20hope%20will%20go%20up%20in%20value%2C%20and%20they%20can%20cash%20out%20and%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20models%20of%20housing%20construction%20in%20US%20cities%20right%20now%2C%20Gray%20said.%20There%20are%20cities%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20New%20York%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20Los%20Angeles%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20are%20building%20very%20little%20new%20housing%20per%20capita.%20Then%20there%20are%20cities%2C%20including%20Sunbelt%20boom%20towns%20like%20Phoenix%2C%20Houston%2C%20and%20Atlanta%2C%C2%A0that%20are%20mostly%20building%20sprawl.%20And%20then%20there%20are%20cities%20like%20Denver%2C%20Seattle%2C%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20that%20are%20successfully%20building%20a%20lot%20of%20new%2C%20denser%20housing%20in%20existing%20neighborhoods.%20He's%20optimistic%20about%20the%20third%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20those%20cities%20share%20is%20a%20shared%20long-term%20recognition%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20grow%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20let's%20start%20doing%20the%20infrastructure%20planning%20and%20the%20public-amenity%20planning%20to%20make%20that%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legalization%20of%20accessory-dwelling%20units%20%E2%80%94%20smaller%2C%20detached%20homes%20like%20backyard%20%26quot%3Bgranny%20flats%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20California%20and%20in%20a%20few%20US%20cities%2C%20including%20Seattle%20and%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fishanbhatt42.github.io%2Ffiles%2Fpaper_adu.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Every%20successful%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20spurring%20construction.%20California%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F05%2F21%2Fadu-granny-flat-california-housing-crisis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproved%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%2023%2C000%20ADU%20permits%20in%202022%2C%20up%20from%20fewer%20than%205%2C000%20in%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20there's%20been%20such%20extreme%20developer%20response%20to%20allowing%20the%20construction%20of%20ADUs%20suggests%20that%20there's%20something%20going%20right%20about%20that%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20Yonah%20Freemark%2C%20a%20land%20use%20and%20housing%20researcher%20at%20the%20Urban%20Institute%2C%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston%20also%20dramatically%20increased%20density%20by%20cutting%20its%20minimum%20home%20lot%20size%20from%205%2C000%20to%201%2C400%20square%20feet%20in%201998.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fpolicy-briefs%2Flearning-houstons-townhouse-reforms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlmost%2080%2C000%20new%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20since%20been%C2%A0built%20on%20these%20smaller%20lots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20townhome%20is%20shown%20for%20sale%20on%20Freund%20St.%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20April%2013%2C%202022%20in%20Houston.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cd2f928df5080019d31243%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHouston%20has%20been%20one%20of%20America's%20housing%20success%20stories%3A%20A%20reduction%20of%20its%20minimum%20lot%20size%20has%20allowed%20homes%20to%20be%20built%20more%20densely.%3Cp%3EBrett%20Coomer%2FHouston%20Chronicle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20are%20signs%20zoning%20reform%20is%20appealing%20to%20different%20geographies%20and%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum.%20Progressive%20blue%20state%20YIMBYs%2C%20libertarians%2C%20and%20free-market%20conservatives%20have%20all%20gotten%20behind%20versions%20of%20it.%20Montana%20Republicans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-republicans-anti-california-message-pro-housing-affordability-building-density-2023-4%5C%22%3Erecently%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20slew%20of%20bills%20loosening%20zoning%20across%20the%20state%2C%20framing%20the%20effort%20as%20a%20way%20to%20avoid%20California-style%20sprawl.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFlexibility%20in%20messaging%20is%20one%20of%20the%20real%20strengths%20of%20the%20pro-housing%20movement%2C%26quot%3B%20Schuetz%2C%20of%20the%20Brookings%20Institute%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20California%2C%20you%20can%20frame%20this%20as%20about%20racial%20equity%2C%20about%20climate%20friendliness.%20In%20Montana%2C%20you%20can%20say%20this%20is%20the%20anti-California.%20Utah%20is%20very%20focused%20on%20their%20scarcity%20of%20water%20and%20also%20very%20much%20on%20family-friendly%20areas%2C%20making%20it%20feasible%20for%20kids%20to%20move%20back%20to%20the%20places%20where%20they%20grew%20up.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReforms%20don't%20always%20work%20in%20one%20fell%20swoop%2C%20though.%20In%202018%2C%20Minneapolis%20became%20the%20first%20major%20US%20city%20to%20institute%20Auckland-style%20reforms%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F12%2F13%2Fus%2Fminneapolis-single-family-zoning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eending%20single-family%20zoning%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20legalizing%20the%20construction%20of%20up%20to%20three%20homes%20on%20a%20single-family%20lot.%20But%20the%20city%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fternercenter.berkeley.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2FMissing-Middle-Brief-December-2022.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20allow%20new%20multiunit%20buildings%20to%20be%20taller%20or%20wider%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20single-family%20homes%20they%20replaced%2C%20so%20the%20initial%20policy%20changes%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.builderonline.com%2Fland%2Fplanning%2Fhow-eliminating-single-family-only-zoning-will-impact-builders-and-developers_o%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espurred%20just%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20city%20was%20hoping%20for.%20The%20size%20limitations%20make%20the%20option%20less%20financially%20attractive%20to%20developers.%20The%20experience%20proved%20that%20policymakers%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20tweak%20policies%20repeatedly%20to%20get%20their%20desired%20outcomes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20devil%20is%20in%20the%20details%2C%26quot%3B%20Been%2C%20the%20former%20New%20York%20City%20deputy%20mayor%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20gazillion%20details.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20spite%20of%20some%20hiccups%2C%20Been%20added%2C%20the%20early%20success%20of%20these%20zoning%20reforms%20is%20promising.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20seeing%20the%20fruits%20of%20the%20changes%2C%20and%20that's%20really%20affirming%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20doing%20this%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20reforms%2C%20but%20also%20reassuring%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20the%20world%20hasn't%20fallen%20apart%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Beth%20Pyataks%20Accessory%20Dwelling%20Unit%20in%20her%20backyard%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20January%206%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cd306df5d4870019e1cf92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAccessory%20dwelling%20units%20are%20catching%20on%20in%20places%20like%20California%20that%20have%20legalized%20them.%3Cp%3EAllison%20Zaucha%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EUpzoning%20is%20necessary%2C%20but%20not%20sufficient%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZoning%20reform%20is%20just%20one%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle.%20There%20are%20a%20slew%20of%20other%20necessary%20fixes%20to%20get%20the%20US%20to%20housing-market%20nirvana%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20building-code%20changes%20to%20long-term%20expansion%20of%20services%20and%20amenities.%20Cities%20and%20states%20need%20to%20build%20sufficient%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20mass%20transit%2C%20schools%2C%20parks%2C%20water%20and%20sewer%20capacity%2C%20and%20other%20essential%20services%20to%20accommodate%20growing%20communities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20really%20need%20to%20look%20at%20it%20holistically%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20you're%20bringing%20all%20of%20the%20additional%20capacity%20in%20the%20basic%20things%20that%20make%20the%20neighborhood%20feel%20like%20a%20neighborhood%2C%26quot%3B%20Been%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20also%20needs%20to%20invest%20public%20funds%20in%20affordable-housing%20and%20public-housing%20options%20for%20lower-income%20people.%20Without%20subsidies%20for%20more%20inclusive%20housing%2C%20people%20who%20can't%20afford%20market-rate%20homes%20will%20be%20left%20behind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20housing%20supply%20is%20almost%20an%20unambiguous%20positive%2C%20and%20allowing%20that%20new%20housing%20supply%20through%20government%20regulation%20seems%20extremely%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Freemark%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20said%2C%20we%20can't%20just%20rely%20on%20a%20market-based%20response%20to%20actually%20get%20those%20new%20housing%20units%20to%20be%20built%2C%20because%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20see%20investment%20in%20low-income%20neighborhoods%2C%20and%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20see%20new%20housing%20units%20that%20are%20affordable%20to%20low-%20and%20moderate-income%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20any%20way%20you%20slice%20it%2C%20cities%20need%20to%20build%20more%20housing.%20And%20they%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20voices%20of%20current%20homeowners%20don't%20drown%20out%20those%20of%20generations%20of%20future%20residents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20procedural%20side%20matters%20a%20lot%2C%20because%20if%20you%20give%20existing%20residents%20veto%20power%2C%20they%20can%20show%20up%20at%20community%20meetings%20and%20protest%20things%20and%20drag%20out%20the%20process%20and%20require%20the%20developer%20to%20keep%20making%20changes%20and%20go%20back%20to%20their%20architect%2C%26quot%3B%20Schuetz%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20make%20it%20very%2C%20very%20expensive%20and%20so%20some%20of%20the%20projects%20will%20just%20die%20because%20they're%20no%20longer%20worth%20it.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpzoning%20can%20appeal%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20progressive%20YIMBYs%20to%20conservatives%20who%20want%20less%20government%20regulation.%20New%20Zealand%20shows%20that%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20an%20affordability%20crisis%2C%20it's%20a%20necessary%20first%20step%20to%20bigger%2C%20more%20ambitious%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20incremental%20step%20toward%20upzoning%20is%20a%20positive%20step%20toward%20increasing%20supply%20and%20improving%20affordability%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Hamilton%2C%20a%20housing%20researcher%20at%20the%20libertarian-leaning%20Mercatus%20Center%20at%20George%20Mason%20University%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20an%20overall%20objective%2C%20I%20think%20bringing%20down%20house%20prices%20to%20construction%20costs%20is%20an%20ultimate%20sign%20of%20housing%20abundance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22c19804eacd372b9cf134b701ab612126%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EEliza%20Relman%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20policy%20correspondent%20focused%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rents-home-prices-build-more-houses-new-zealand-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691400481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cd4919f5d4870019e20455%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rents-home-prices-build-more-houses-new-zealand-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20Zealand%20has%20figured%20out%20a%20simple%20way%20to%20build%20lots%20and%20lots%20of%20affordable%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20without%20making%20the%20neighbors%20mad.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-lower-rents-home-prices-build-more-houses-new-zealand-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meesho%20becomes%20first%20horizontal%20e-commerce%20company%20to%20attain%20profitability%22%2C%22content%