lly%20applied%20in%202018%2C%20but%20the%20process%20kept%20getting%20delayed%2C%20even%20though%20I'd%20turned%20in%20all%20the%20paperwork.%20Because%20my%20dad%20works%20at%20a%20military%20base%20in%20Arizona%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20get%20my%20fingerprints%20and%20everything%20else%20that%20was%20required%20of%20me%20very%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20even%20started%20the%202022%20school%20year%20in%20Phoenix%20because%20the%20government%20tells%20you%20not%20to%20quit%20until%20you%20get%20an%20official%20offer.%20But%20after%2014%20weeks%2C%20I%20was%20cleared%20and%20had%20my%20official%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20finally%20moved%20to%20Japan%20in%20December%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20set%20to%20teach%20third%20grade.%20Hindsight%20is%2020%2F20%2C%20but%20I%20should've%20realized%20on%20day%20one%20that%20it%20was%20not%20a%20good%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20arrived%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%20school%20before%20winter%20break%2C%20and%20I%20met%20all%20my%20coworkers%20and%20the%20students.%20Everyone%20introduced%20themselves%2C%20except%20my%20coteacher%20who%20had%20already%20set%20up%20my%20side%20of%20the%20classroom%20the%20way%20he%20wanted.%20It%20created%20a%20hostile%20dynamic%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20I%20met%20up%20over%20break%2C%20but%20the%20conversation%20was%20mostly%20him%20explaining%20to%20me%20how%20he%20runs%20his%20classroom.%20When%20school%20started%20up%20again%2C%20we%20continued%20to%20have%20problems.%20Dividing%20tasks%20in%20the%20classroom%20was%20difficult%2C%20and%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20sponsor%20I%20had%20through%20the%20program's%20teacher%20group%20to%20help%20me%20work%20through%20some%20of%20the%20responsibilities%20he%20gave%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20having%20a%20meeting%20with%20the%20principal%20at%20the%20end%20of%20January%20to%20discuss%20the%20situation%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20tension%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20of%20my%20coworkers%20were%20American%2C%20there%20was%20tension%20between%20those%20who%20were%20considered%20local%20hires%2C%20like%20military%20spouses%2C%20and%20those%20of%20us%20who%20were%20CONUS%20%E2%80%94%20or%20continental-US-hires%20who%20came%20from%20the%20United%20States%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sensed%20a%20definite%20dislike%20for%20those%20in%20my%20situation.%20I%20was%20given%20a%20lot%20of%20benefits%20like%20a%20cost-of-living%20allowance%20and%20a%20living-quarters%20allowance%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20living%20expenses%2C%20plus%20I%20got%20my%20normal%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20no%20support%20from%20administration.%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20recorded%20conversations%20because%20sometimes%20it%20felt%20like%20people%20would%20say%20something%20to%20my%20face%20and%20then%20I'd%20get%20an%20email%20saying%20something%20completely%20different.%20I%20was%20constantly%20asking%20them%20to%20observe%20me%20in%20the%20classroom%20to%20see%20what%20my%20coteaching%20situation%20was%20like%20firsthand%2C%20but%20they%20either%20wouldn't%20show%20up%20or%20they%20showed%20up%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20my%20work%20experience%2C%20I%20had%20a%20great%20time%20in%20Japan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20woman%20takes%20a%20selfie%20in%20Japan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cbfa770f3dff0019569eab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStultz%20exploring%20in%20Japan.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brianna%20Stultz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20visiting%20all%20the%20shrines%20and%20castles.%20I%20also%20lived%20right%20off%20the%20ocean%2C%20which%20was%20fantastic%20having%20grown%20up%20in%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20the%20food%20was%20downright%20amazing.%20I%20also%20met%20a%20friend%20through%20work%20who%20I'm%20absolutely%20devastated%20that%20I'm%20not%20going%20be%20able%20to%20see%20all%20the%20time%20now.%20I%20knew%20my%20job%20itself%20was%20toxic%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20stay%20so%20badly%20I%20was%20willing%20to%20ignore%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20semester%2C%20I%20still%20thought%20I%20would%20be%20coming%20back%20for%20the%20next%20school%20year%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20administration%20would%20be%20moving%20me%20to%20another%20grade%20level%20because%20they'd%20heard%20from%20other%20staff%20members%20how%20toxic%20the%20grade%20level%20I%20was%20teaching%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20instead%20they%20fired%20me%20in%20May%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%2C%20among%20them%20the%20inability%20to%20collaborate%20effectively%20with%20my%20coteacher.%20I%20was%20completely%20blindsided.%20I%20felt%20targeted%20and%20believe%20I%20was%20unfairly%20fired%2C%20but%20I%20was%20a%20probationary%20teacher%20so%20I%20had%20very%20few%20protections.%20I%20could've%20filed%20a%20claim%20with%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission%3Cstrong%3E%20(%3C%2Fstrong%3EEEOC)%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20was%20worth%20fighting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20angry%20and%20crying%2C%20but%20my%20grief%20only%20lasted%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20and%20then%20turned%20straight%20to%20anger%20because%20of%20the%20unfairness%20of%20the%20whole%20situation.%20I%20wondered%20why%20my%20principal%20even%20hired%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20expenses%20and%20stress%20of%20being%20fired%20and%20being%20forced%20to%20move%20again%20has%20been%20a%20lot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20left%20my%20district%20in%20Arizona%2C%20I%20was%20charged%20a%20fee%20for%20breaking%20my%20contract%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20I%20paid%20thousands%20to%20move%20to%20Japan.%20I%20also%20owe%20my%20parents%20money%20for%20helping%20me%20o