%20company%20doesn't%20currently%20ship%20to%20the%20US.%20Fast%20Retailing%20plans%20to%20open%20200%20stores%20in%20North%20America%20within%20five%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.japantimes.co.jp%2Fnews%2F2022%2F08%2F05%2Fbusiness%2Fcorporate-business%2Fgu-store-new-york%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJapan%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-gu-fashion-clothing-brand%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691398801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cbfacd0f3dff0019569f2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-gu-fashion-clothing-brand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22GU%2C%20Uniqlo's%20sister%20brand%2C%20gains%20popularity%20among%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20shoppers%20in%20the%20US.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jortakales%40insider.com%20(Jennifer%20Ortakales%20Dawkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-gu-fashion-clothing-brand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20landed%20a%20job%20at%20Google%20right%20out%20of%20college.%20Here%20are%2010%20things%20I%20wish%20I%20knew%20before%20starting%20my%20career.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22791%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Charlene%20Lee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d08b8ef5d4870019e2bf4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22593%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECharlene%20Lee%20says%20she%20used%20to%20schedule%20tasks%20in%2025-minute%20increments%20per%20the%20Pomodoro%20technique%2C%20but%20later%20learned%20about%20managing%20her%20energy%20instead%20of%20her%20time.%3Cp%3ECharlene%20Lee%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECharlene%20Lee%20is%20a%20former%20product%20manager%20at%20Google%20who%20wishes%20she%20had%20a%20guide%20prior%20to%20starting%20her%20first%20job.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShe%20shares%20a%20few%20lessons%20she's%20learned%20throughout%20her%20career%2C%20like%20that%20i%3Cstrong%3Et's%20more%20useful%20to%20manage%20your%20energy%20instead%20of%20your%20time.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELee%20also%20learned%20that%20promotions%20are%20an%20arbitrary%20yardstick%20based%20on%20someone%20else's%20definition%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20remember%20the%20day%20the%20recruiter%20called%20me%20with%20a%20job%20offer%20from%20Google.%20I%20danced%20around%20my%20dorm%20room%20for%20hours%20celebrating%20what%20was%20to%20come.%20Landing%20a%20position%20in%20Google's%20coveted%20Associate%20Manager%20program%20was%20a%20dream%2C%20and%20all%20the%20years%20of%20late-night%20problem%20sets%20and%20internships%20were%20finally%20paying%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20summer%20passed%20and%20my%20first%20day%20neared%2C%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20unease%20and%20anxiety%20began%20to%20set%20in.%20Leaving%20the%20structure%20of%20school%20introduced%20a%20new%2C%20overwhelming%20kind%20of%20freedom.%20I%20imagined%20myself%20struggling%20to%20both%20fit%20in%20and%20stand%20out%20among%20people%20who%20were%20older%20and%20more%20experienced%20than%20me.%20I%20kept%20wishing%20for%20a%20guide%20to%20entering%20the%20workplace%20for%20the%20first%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20a%20decade%20has%20passed%20since%20I%20got%20that%20call%20in%20my%20college%20dorm.%20Today%2C%20I'd%20like%20to%20share%20some%20of%20the%20lessons%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20learned%20before%20starting%20my%20career%2C%20lessons%20that%20I%20now%20teach%20my%20team.%20This%20is%20the%20result%20of%20hours%20of%201%3A1s%2C%20books%2C%20and%20trial%20and%20error.%20It's%20the%20guide%20I%20wish%20I'd%20had%20when%20I%20began%20my%20journey.%20I%20hope%20it%20will%20benefit%20you%20in%20the%20ways%20that%20it%20would've%20helped%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20It's%20your%20job%20to%20find%20a%20good%20manager%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20best%20managers%2C%20Paul%2C%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20with%20me%20early%20in%20my%20career.%20He%20wasn't%20just%20great%20because%20he%20did%20things%20I%20valued%20in%20leaders%2C%20like%20inspiring%20others%20with%20bold%20ideas%20and%20celebrating%20his%20team%20instead%20of%20himself.%20I've%20had%20plenty%20of%20managers%20who%20did%20(and%20didn't)%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20was%20great%20because%20he%20loved%20to%20teach.%20Our%201%3A1s%20covered%20a%20lot%2C%20from%20the%20more%20straightforward%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20you%20frame%20a%20problem%20for%20an%20executive%3F%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20more%20complicated%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20should%20you%20do%20with%20your%20life%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20taught%20me%20to%20be%20curious%20and%20look%20for%20signs%20of%20rising%20stress%2C%20and%20how%20to%20reset%20if%20a%20meeting%20didn't%20go%20the%20way%20I%20wanted.%20He%20taught%20me%20skills%20and%20ways%20of%20thinking%20that%20a%20college%20degree%20couldn't%20have.%20But%20connecting%20with%20Paul%20didn't%20happen%20by%20accident.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20my%20career%2C%20I%20heard%20how%20important%20it%20was%20to%20%26quot%3Bhave%20a%20good%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20I%20had%20no%20clue%20what%20that%20meant.%20I%20assumed%20that%20someone%20who%20was%20likable%20and%20tenured%20also%20managed%20well.%20I%20also%20assumed%20I%20had%20no%20choice%20in%20who%20became%20my%20manager.%20I%20was%20wrong.%20If%20I%20wanted%20a%20good%20manager%2C%20it%20was%20my%20job%20to%20find%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20by%20meeting%20with%20managers%20I%20admired%20and%20seeing%20if%20how%20they%20dispensed%20knowledge%20resonated%20with%20me.%20In%20my%20first%2030-minute%20chat%20with%20Paul%2C%20I%20learned%20so%20much%2C%20and%20to%20my%20surprise%2C%20he%20said%20that%20he%20did%2C%20too.%20It%20was%20clear%20he%20was%20a%20good%20teacher%20but%20also%20that%20it%20was%20a%20two-way%20relationship.%20Learning%20from%20him%20compounded%20like%20an%20investment%2C%20one%20that%20continues%20to%20grow%20to%20this%20day.%20I%20owe%20it%20all%20to%20finding%20a%20great%20manager.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Check%20your%20values%20instead%20of%20boxes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20whole%20life%2C%20I%20operated%20like%20a%20box-checker.%20Get%20into%20college%2C%20get%20a%20good%20job%2C%20get%20promoted%2C%20and%20become%20a%20manager.%20After%20I%20checked%20one%20box%2C%20I%20moved%20on%20to%20the%20next%20one.%20Things%20changed%20when%20the%20next%20box%2C%20like%20writing%20a%20book%2C%20started%20conflicting%20with%20things%20that%20weren't%20on%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20me%20almost%20a%20decade%20to%20stop%20forcing%20myself%20down%20the%20%26quot%3Bcorrect%20path.%26quot%3B%20Of%20my%20most%20consequential%20life%20decisions%2C%20the%20best%20ones%20were%20driven%20by%20my%20gut%20rather%20than%20my%20brain.%20I%20did%20a%20fellowship%2C%20worked%20abroad%20in%20Asia%2C%20and%20studied%20Chinese.%20These%20were%20decisions%20defined%20by%20my%20values%2C%20and%20not%20necessarily%20what%20%26quot%3Bmade%20the%20most%20sense.%26quot%3B%20I%20pursued%20these%20experiences%20to%20become%20one%20percent%20better%20and%20to%20give%20back%20to%20others.%20Each%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20know%20how%2C%20or%20even%20if%2C%20these%20experiences%20would%20impact%20my%20career.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.stanford.edu%2F2005%2F06%2F12%2Fyouve-got-find-love-jobs-says%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt's%20only%20now%2C%20as%20I%20look%20back%2C%20that%20I%20can%20connect%20the%20dots%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20easy%20to%20go%20down%20paths%20that%20were%20well-lit%20but%20just%20weren't%20for%20me.%20Asking%20myself%20what%20I%20valued%20was%20challenging%20because%20it%20meant%20being%20honest%20about%20my%20definition%20of%20success.%20I%20sometimes%20still%20struggle%20with%20this%2C%20but%20when%20I%20get%20stuck%2C%20I%20know%20to%20check%20my%20values.%20Only%20once%20I%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fchoose-your-own-adventure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderstand%20what%20matters%20to%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20I%20chart%20a%20path%20to%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Measure%20yourself%20with%20your%20own%20yardstick%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20switch%20roles%20a%20few%20years%20into%20my%20job%20at%20Google.%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20on%20a%20new%20product%20and%20move%20from%20Asia%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20but%20doing%20so%20meant%20I%20would%20forego%20a%20promotion.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20huge%20setback%20to%20watch%20my%20peers%20progress%20up%20the%20ladder%20while%20I%20didn't.%20I%20still%20went%20through%20with%20it%2C%20but%20for%20the%20next%20year%2C%20I%20worried%20that%20I%20had%20stunted%20my%20career.%20For%20a%20while%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20because%20the%20next%20promotion%20took%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fget-off-the-treadmill-and-onto-the%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBut%20promotions%20are%20an%20arbitrary%20yardstick%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20someone%20else's%20definition%20of%20growth.%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20clarified%20to%20myself%20earlier%20what%20my%20yardstick%20was%20and%20reminded%20myself%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Frun-your-own-race%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erun%20my%20own%20race%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20would%20have%20saved%20me%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20late-night%20angst%20and%20rumination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20that%20decision%2C%20I%20achieved%20growth%20by%20working%20on%20a%20product%20I%20loved%20and%20living%20in%20New%20York%20in%20my%2020s.%20I%20might%20have%20made%20a%20move%20that%20seemed%20like%20a%20step%20backward%20to%20others.%20But%20to%20me%2C%20that%20decision%20put%20me%20three%20steps%20forward%20because%20of%20how%20I%20defined%20progress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Plan%20to%20learn%20instead%20of%20over-planning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20been%20an%20over-planner.%20I%20used%20to%20map%20out%20my%20five-year%20plan%20every%20six%20months%20on%20a%20legal-sized%20sheet%20of%20paper%20and%20bring%20it%20to%20my%20managers%20to%20discuss.%20I%20thought%20the%20only%20way%20to%20reach%20my%20goals%20was%20to%20plan%20them%20out%20step-by-step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20overplanning%20stressed%20me%20out%20when%20things%20inevitably%20didn't%20go%20according%20to%20plan.%20I%20would%20take%20every%20blip%20as%20a%20sign%20that%20I%20hadn't%20worked%20hard%20enough.%20Then%20I%20would%20overcorrect%20by%20planning%20even%20more%20when%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20many%20things%20were%20out%20of%20my%20control.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20overplanning%20almost%20made%20me%20miss%20unexpected%20opportunities.%20Had%20I%20stuck%20to%20my%20original%20plan%20to%20go%20to%20business%20school%20at%2026%2C%20I%20would%20have%20missed%20out%20on%20working%20in%20China%20and%20building%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Fproducts%2Fmaps%2Fspeak-easy-while-traveling%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Translate%20within%20Google%20Maps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20ended%20up%20being%20the%20experiences%20I%20learned%20from%20the%20most.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20preparation%20and%20self-discovery%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fpm-your-career-like-you-pm-your-product%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enecessary%20tools%20to%20plan%20your%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20balance%20between%20thoughtful%20planning%20and%20getting%20stuck%20in%20over-analysis.%20Careers%20are%20long%2C%20and%20they%20can%20take%20many%20shapes.%20Instead%20of%20approaching%20each%20decision%20as%20right%20or%20wrong%2C%20I%20now%20use%20my%20values%20to%20reframe%20it%20as%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20much%20can%20I%20learn%20from%20this%20opportunity%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Give%20sponsors%20a%20reason%20to%20help%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20used%20to%20be%E2%80%94and%20sometimes%20still%20am%E2%80%94shy%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20people%20whom%20I%20respect%20and%20admire.%20I%20used%20to%20watch%20my%20more%20confident%20peers%20go%20up%20and%20introduce%20themselves%20to%20senior%20leaders%2C%20while%20my%20default%20was%20to%20stay%20in%20my%20seat%20and%20assume%20that%20senior%20people%20wouldn't%20help%20me%20because%20I%20had%20nothing%20to%20offer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fcurate-cultivate-and-create-things%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI've%20stopped%20holding%20myself%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20realizing%20that%20help%20can%20take%20many%20forms.%20For%20my%20second%20year%20of%20Google's%20new%20grad%20program%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20learn%20about%20potential%20teams%20to%20join%20at%20our%20Asia%20headquarters%20in%20Singapore.%20To%20be%20helpful%2C%20I%20offered%20to%20contribute%20to%20an%20internal%20newsletter%20that%20one%20manager%2C%20Jon%2C%20published%20each%20week.%20Though%20Jon%20wasn't%20hiring%2C%20that%20relationship%20opened%20doors%20to%20another%20team.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20continued%20to%20volunteer%20to%20help%20with%20anything%20I%20thought%20was%20interesting%20or%20could%20be%20beneficial.%20I%20raised%20my%20hand%20to%20run%20a%20development%20training%20for%20the%20region%2C%20led%20an%20international%20study%20trip%2C%20hosted%20women's%20ERG%20breakfasts%2C%20and%20organized%20a%20hackathon.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20joining%20Jon's%20team.%20He%20then%20helped%20me%20land%20an%20opportunity%20to%20work%20in%20Shanghai%20with%20a%20director%20I%20had%20met%20during%20the%20training%20I'd%20organized.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contributing%20to%20the%20community%2C%20I%20built%20relationships%20with%20people%20like%20Jon%2C%20who%20became%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fhow-to-find-a-sponsor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20my%20biggest%20sponsors%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20catapulted%20me%20to%20my%20next%20goal.%20I%20now%20always%20try%20to%20help%20others%20first%20before%20asking%20for%20help%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Take%20the%20risk%20and%20show%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20my%20career%2C%20I've%20cared%20about%20supporting%20young%20women%2C%20but%20I%20never%20used%20to%20publicize%20it.%20I%20cringed%20sharing%20about%20it%20on%20social%20media%2C%20thinking%20it%20was%20calculative%20and%20self-inflating.%20But%20then%20I%20saw%20how%20peers%20who%20shared%20their%20work%20were%20more%20effective%20at%20achieving%20their%20goals%20because%20people%20remembered%20who%20they%20were%20and%20recommended%20them%20to%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20reputation%20existed%2C%20whether%20I%20liked%20it%20or%20not.%20By%20staying%20quiet%2C%20I%20was%20creating%20one%20that%20was%20neutral%20at%20best%20and%20forgettable%20at%20worst.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fstop-using-ridiculous-strategies%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20was%20sabotaging%20myself%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20people%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20help%20me%20on%20my%20journey%20if%20they%20didn't%20know%20what%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20finally%20took%20the%20plunge%20by%20sharing%20my%20learnings%20onstage%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwomenpm.org%2Fconference%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWomen%20In%20Product%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20posting%20about%20it%20online.%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20amount%20of%20interest%20and%20new%20connections%20I%20made%20by%20taking%20the%20risk%20and%20showing%20up.%20I%20still%20hesitate%20to%20put%20things%20out%20in%20public%E2%80%94including%20this%20article%E2%80%94but%20I%20am%20only%20able%20to%20make%20the%20impact%20I%20want%20by%20sharing%20my%20work%20with%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20See%20your%20team%20as%20real%20people%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20getting%20things%20done.%20Early%20on%2C%20I%20focused%20on%20my%20work%20and%20assumed%20my%20colleagues'%20way%20of%20working%20was%20the%20same%20as%20mine.%20I%20then%20got%20frustrated%20when%20they%20didn't%20stay%20as%20late%20as%20I%20did%20or%20reply%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20wanted.%20I%20rolled%20up%20my%20sleeves%20and%20did%20things%20myself%2C%20thinking%20I%20was%20proving%20that%20I%20was%20capable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20not%20collaborating%2C%20I%20was%20redoing%20work%20and%20creating%20knowledge%20silos.%20One%20peer%20mentioned%20that%20despite%20my%20work%20ethic%2C%20I%20could%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bbulldozer.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20both%20shocked%20and%20humbled.%20It%20wasn't%20only%20what%20I%20got%20done%20that%20mattered%3B%20it%20was%20how%20I%20did%20it%20with%20others.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fa-guide-for-onboarding-into-a-new%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20hadn't%20earned%20my%20team's%20trust%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20didn't%20know%20about%20their%20families%20or%20what%20they%20cared%20about%20because%20I%20had%20never%20asked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20the%20next%20year%20learning%20who%20my%20co-workers%20were%20outside%20the%20office%20and%20beyond%20their%20work%20goals.%20Getting%20to%20know%20my%20team%20as%20real%20people%20helped%20me%20not%20only%20get%20things%20done%20but%20also%20become%20a%20better%20teammate%20and%20leader.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Manage%20your%20energy%2C%20not%20your%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20have%20called%20me%20a%20%26quot%3Bproductivity%20junkie.%26quot%3B%20I%20used%20to%20schedule%20my%20tasks%20in%2025-minute%20increments%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPomodoro_Technique%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPomodoro%20technique%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20replying%20to%20texts%2C%20going%20to%20the%20gym%2C%20and%20reading%20the%20news.%20My%20output%20increased%2C%20but%20I%20somehow%20felt%20that%20I%20had%20less%20time.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20my%20energy%20was%20depleted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20heard%20Naval%20Ravikant%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20AngelList%2C%20say%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalmanack.com%2Falmanack-of-naval-ravikant%2Fchoosing-to-care-for-yourself%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20number%20one%20priority%20in%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94above%20his%20happiness%2C%20his%20family%2C%20and%20his%20work%E2%80%94was%20his%20health.%20The%20maxim%20that%20%26quot%3Byou%20can't%20pour%20from%20an%20empty%20cup%26quot%3B%20finally%20made%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnergy%2C%20not%20time%2C%20became%20the%20currency%20that%20I%20started%20to%20save%20and%20protect%20before%20I%20decided%20where%20to%20spend%20it.%20Things%20I%20thought%20I%20had%20no%20time%20for%E2%80%94exercising%2C%20taking%20walks%2C%20socializing%E2%80%94became%20my%20top%20investments%20to%20recharge%20my%20mind%20and%20body.%20I%20became%20aware%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fcurate-cultivate-and-create-things%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunconscious%20things%20I%20did%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20sapping%20my%20energy%20and%20taking%20up%20valuable%20mind%20space%2C%20like%20ruminating.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2007%2F10%2Fmanage-your-energy-not-your-time%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManaging%20my%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20helped%20me%20use%20my%20time%20more%20meaningfully%20and%20productively.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Make%20your%20call%20to%20action%20clear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20of%20my%20first%20products%2C%20I%20created%20a%20deck%20with%20robust%20data%20and%20facts%20on%20how%20to%20grow%20market%20share.%20My%20manager%2C%20Carissa%2C%20was%20curious%20about%20some%20trends%2C%20but%20she%20also%20asked%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20what%3F%26quot%3B%20Despite%20my%20many%20slides%2C%20I%20hadn't%20communicated%20what%20I%20wanted%20my%20audience%2C%20the%20engineering%20lead%20of%20another%20team%2C%20to%20do.%20Did%20I%20need%20them%20to%20help%20me%20secure%20more%20resources%20or%20agree%20to%20collaborate%20with%20us%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20didn't%20make%20my%20call%20to%20action%20clear%2C%20nothing%20I%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fcommunicating-so-your-message-lands%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanded%20with%20my%20audience%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20get%20them%20to%20buy%20into%20my%20idea%2C%20I%20needed%20them%20to%20feel%20like%20they%20were%20part%20of%20the%20journey.%20To%20get%20them%20excited%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20tell%20a%20story%20around%20my%20data%20that%20would%20motivate%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20ideas%20and%20plans%20were%20only%20as%20good%20as%20how%20I%20communicated%20them.%20Carissa%20wasn't%20able%20to%20do%20anything%20with%20what%20I%20said%20because%20she%20didn't%20understand%20what%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20say%E2%80%94or%20even%20why%20it%20was%20important.%20Now%20I%20always%20start%20every%20presentation%20not%20with%20what%20I%20want%20my%20audience%20to%20take%20away%2C%20but%20with%20what%20I%20want%20them%20to%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E10.%20Celebrate%20your%20wins%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20looked%20at%20a%20five-year%20plan%20I%20made%20when%20I%20was%2023.%20I%20was%20surprised%20that%20I%20had%20accomplished%20most%20of%20the%20things%20on%20the%20list.%20When%20my%20partner%2C%20Marty%2C%20jokingly%20asked%20if%20I%20had%20forgotten%20about%20my%20achievements%2C%20I%20had%20to%20admit%20that%20I%20rarely%20recognize%20what%20I've%20done.%20Because%20I've%20always%20equated%20celebrations%20with%20complacency%2C%20I've%20always%20set%20new%20goals%20to%20strive%20for%20next%20rather%20than%20celebrating%20my%20wins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20success%20trap%20of%20moving%20goalposts%2C%20or%20what%20Harvard%20professor%20Dan%20Gilbert%20calls%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwaitbutwhy.com%2F2013%2F11%2Flife-is-picture-but-you-live-in-pixel.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BImpact%20Bias.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20You're%20never%20as%20happy%20as%20you%20think%20you'll%20be%20when%20you%20achieve%20a%20goal%20because%20the%20mind%20adapts%20to%20your%20current%20circumstances.%20This%20%26quot%3Bhedonic%20adaptation%26quot%3B%20created%20an%20endless%20cycle%20of%20me%20being%20dissatisfied%20with%20my%20progress%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fovercoming-imposter-syndrome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeeling%20like%20an%20imposter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20skeptical%20when%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finbaldemri.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20coach%2C%20Inbal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20insisted%20that%20celebrating%20my%20wins%20could%20help%20me%20better%20achieve%20my%20goals.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20was%20my%20constant%20determination%20to%20achieve%20that%20had%20gotten%20me%20to%20where%20I%20was.%20But%20she%20showed%20me%20how%20celebrating%20could%20help%20me%20pause%20and%20pinpoint%20patterns%2C%20which%20I%20could%20then%20recreate.%20Remembering%20how%20I%20had%20prevailed%20in%20the%20past%20helped%20me%20strengthen%20my%20conviction%20to%20overcome%20current%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThoughtful%20celebration%20wasn't%20self-indulgent%3B%20rather%2C%20it%20was%20a%20powerful%20tool%20for%20sustaining%20my%20long-term%20growth.%20I've%20learned%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20when%20I%20fall%20into%20this%20unforgiving%20cycle%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdebliu.substack.com%2Fp%2Fovercoming-imposter-syndrome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estriving%20for%20perfection%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20now%20ask%20myself%20if%20the%20%26quot%3Bme%20from%20a%20decade%20ago%26quot%3B%20would%20be%20proud%20of%20who%20I%20am%20today%2C%20and%20I%20celebrate%20that%20the%20answer%20is%20yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavigating%20the%20beginning%20of%20my%20career%20felt%20intimidating%20and%20isolating%20at%20times%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20less%20alone%20when%20I%20met%20others%20who%20were%20on%20the%20same%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20recruiting%20in%20college%2C%20my%20brother%20gave%20me%20a%20card%20with%20a%20quote%20from%20Ralph%20Waldo%20Emerson%3A%20%26quot%3BLife%20is%20a%20journey%2C%20not%20a%20destination.%26quot%3B%20The%20start%20of%20your%20career%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20your%20journey%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20that%20this%20guide%20helps%20you%20with%20yours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D5cfcceeba7773f74efed95755ead641ecef137a2435a1bc7ad13999dec00d952%26postID%3D64cd37bf8e16d4f2bfc33532%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252