g%20them.%20But%20in%20such%20encounters%2C%20there%20are%20losses%20on%20both%20sides%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20what%20has%20changed%20now%2C%20Mr%20Baghel%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BEarlier%2C%20the%20villagers%2C%20especially%20in%20Bastar%2C%20had%20lost%20faith%20in%20the%20government.%20They%20were%20losing%20their%20land%2C%20even%20water%20bodies%20were%20captured.%20They%20felt%20they%20were%20not%20getting%20the%20right%20price%20for%20their%20produce.%20They%20felt%20deprived%20of%20education%2C%20other%20welfare%20measures.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20security%20personnel%20thought%20that%20anyone%20outside%20their%20camp%20was%20a%20Maoist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20trust%20deficit.%20The%20biggest%20change%20is%20that%20we%20tried%20to%20win%20their%20(villagers')%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Baghel%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%20then%20detailed%20his%20government's%20steps%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20villagers%2C%20including%20an%20exercise%20to%20return%20land%20to%20tribals.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20given%2018%20lakh%20hectares%20to%20villagers.%20This%20is%20unprecedented.%20This%20has%20not%20happened%20anywhere%20in%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Baghel%20also%20detailed%20how%20his%20government's%20steps%20how%20helped%20millet%20farmers%20and%20the%20mahua%20industry.%20Mahua%20refers%20to%20a%20flower%20used%20to%20make%20an%20alcoholic%20beverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691398500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fn4t2drb8_bhupesh-baghel-interview_625x300_07_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbhupesh-baghel-chhattisgarh-maoists-left-wing-extremism-bhupesh-baghel-on-what-has-changed-in-chhattisgarhs-fight-against-maoists-4276045%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Maoists%20have%20now%20been%20surrounded%20and%20people's%20faith%20in%20the%20government%20machinery%20has%20been%20restored%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20Chief%20Minister%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%20said%20today%20while%20listing%20his%20government's%20achievements%20in%20fighting%20Left%20Wing%20Extremism.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbhupesh-baghel-chhattisgarh-maoists-left-wing-extremism-bhupesh-baghel-on-what-has-changed-in-chhattisgarhs-fight-against-maoists-4276045%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbhupesh-baghel-chhattisgarh-maoists-left-wing-extremism-bhupesh-baghel-on-what-has-changed-in-chhattisgarhs-fight-against-maoists-4276045%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbhupesh-baghel-chhattisgarh-maoists-left-wing-extremism-bhupesh-baghel-on-what-has-changed-in-chhattisgarhs-fight-against-maoists-4276045%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20A%20Plan%20For%20Bursting%20Shimla%20Draws%20Huge%20Objections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EShimla%2C%20the%20queen%20of%20hills%2C%20was%20once%20the%20summer%20capital%20of%20the%20British.%20It%20was%20originally%20planned%20for%20a%20population%20of%2025%2C000.%20The%20British%20planned%20Shimla%20strictly%20in%20consonance%20with%20its%20contours%20and%20levels%20of%20topography.%20Cut%20to%20the%20present%20-%20unplanned%20and%20indiscriminate%20development%20in%20the%20core%2C%20non-core%2C%20green%20and%20rural%20areas%20within%20the%20Shimla%20planning%20area%20has%20given%20rise%20to%20serious%20environmental%20and%20ecological%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20population%20of%20Shimla%20is%20around%202.41%20lakh%2C%20as%20of%20Census%202011%2C%20besides%20a%20floating%20population%20of%20some%2070%2C000%20tourists%20per%20day%20during%20peak%20season.%20The%20hill%20station%20lacks%20a%20public%20transport%20system%2C%20parking%20space%20and%20pedestrian%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20draft%20Shimla%20Development%20Plan%20(SDP)%20was%20commissioned%20to%20ensure%20Shimla's%20sustainable%20growth%20and%20expansion%2C%20keeping%20in%20mind%20its%20ecological%20and%20topographical%20challenges.%20The%20SDP%20will%20supersede%20the%20Interim%201979%20plan%2C%20which%20guided%20development%20work%20in%20the%20Shimla%20Municipal%20area.%20The%20new%20plan%20includes%20areas%20around%20Shimla%20such%20as%20Kufri%2C%20Shoghi%20and%20Ghanahatti%20special%20areas%20and%20additional%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20government%20issued%20the%20draft%20SDP%20in%20June%2C%20aiming%20to%20regulate%20construction%20activities%20in%20the%20city.%20The%20plan%20was%20approved%20by%20the%20previous%20government%20in%20February%202022%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20materialise%20as%20the%20National%20Green%20Tribunal%20(NGT)%20held%20it%2C%20terming%20it%20illegal%20and%20in%20conflict%20with%20orders%20in%202017%20to%20regulate%20haphazard%20construction%20in%20Shimla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20SDP%20was%20approved%20again%20after%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20on%20May%203.%20The%20top%20court%20had%20asked%20the%20state%20government%20to%20decide%20on%20the%2097%20objections%20received%20on%20the%20draft%20development%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20stressed%20that%20it%20would%20examine%20the%20plan%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20balancing%20development%20and%20environment.%20The%20case%20will%20come%20up%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SDP%2C%20named%20Vision%202041%2C%20once%20implemented%2C%20will%20permit%20construction%20in%2017%20green%20belts%20with%20certain%20restrictions%2C%20and%20also%20in%20the%20core%20area%20where%20construction%20activity%20was%20banned%20by%20the%20National%20Green%20Tribunal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tribunal%20had%20appointed%20an%20expert%20committee%20to%20study%20the%20impact%20of%20existing%20structures%20on%20the%20environment%20and%20ecology%2C%20sewage%20system%20and%20water%20supply%20of%20Shimla%20in%202015.%20The%20draft%20plan%20ignores%20the%20committee's%20report%20of%202017%2C%20which%20pointed%20out%20that%20Shimla%20had%20far%20exceeded%20its%20carrying%20capacity%20from%20a%20disaster%20risk%20management%20viewpoint.%20Unbridled%20and%20unsafe%20constructions%20on%20slopes%20exceeding%2070%20degrees%20has%20made%20the%20hill%20city%20susceptible%20to%20landslides%20during%20rain%20and%20cloudbursts.%20In%20the%20event%20of%20earthquakes%2C%20there%20will%20be%20huge%20loss%20of%20lives%20and%20property%2C%20the%20report%20warned.%20The%20committee%20recommended%20urgent%20decongestion%20of%20Shimla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20a%20hazard%2C%20vulnerability%20and%20risk%20assessment%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20Shimla%20Municipal%20Corporation%2C%20funded%20by%20United%20Nation%20Development%20Programme%20in%202016%2C%20mentioned%20that%2065%25%20of%20some%202%2C795%20buildings%20it%20surveyed%20were%20in%20the%20criteria%20of%20'high%20vulnerability'.%20Similarly%2C%2028%25%20of%20the%20houses%20have%20had%20some%20form%20of%20fire%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20draft%20plan%20is%20approved%2C%20people%20can%20use%20their%20attic%20as%20a%20habitable%20area%20and%20increase%20its%20height%20to%203.5%20metres.%20The%20construction%20of%20a%20one-storey%20structure%20with%20a%20habitable%20attic%20will%20be%20permissible%20in%2017%20green%20belts.%20Two%20storeys%20with%20a%20habitable%20attic%20and%20parking%20in%20core%20areas%2C%20and%20three%20storeys%20with%20parking%20and%20a%20habitable%20attic%20in%20non-core%20areas%2C%20will%20also%20be%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SDP%20is%20completely%20silent%20on%20whether%20the%20core%20infrastructure%20will%20be%20able%20to%20support%20these%20additions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETikender%20Singh%20Panwar%2C%20former%20deputy%20mayor%20of%20Shimla%2C%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20SDP%20is%20inherently%20flawed.%20The%20basic%20flaw%20is%20that%20unlike%20the%20plains%2C%20Shimla%20is%20a%20cone-shaped%20topography%20and%20the%20single%20land%20use%20plan%20applied%20in%20plains%20can't%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20state's%20terrain%20to%20decide%20on%20basic%20infrastructure.%20In%20the%20southeast%20part%20of%20the%20mountain%2C%20the%20rocks%20generally%20tend%20to%20be%20stronger%20than%20in%20the%20northwestern%20part%20and%20therefore%2C%20you%20see%20most%20British%20bungalows%20were%20constructed%20in%20the%20area%20where%20there%20was%20a%20slightly%20stronger%20strata%2C%20and%20they%20did%20not%20go%20beyond%20a%20certain%20height.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20core%20area%2C%20he%20explains%2C%20there%20are%20places%20where%20the%20rock%20is%20strong%20but%20as%20one%20goes%20vertical%20in%20the%20same%20zone%20(high%20traumatized%20zone)%20the%20rock%20is%20extremely%20vulnerable.%20%26quot%3BShimla%20requires%20zonal%20planning%2C%20based%20on%20solid%20scientific%2C%20geological%20findings.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20mapping%20hasn't%20been%20done%20on%20zone%20or%20sub%20zone%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Panwar%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20government's%20official%20data%2C%2091%20people%20lost%20their%20lives%20from%20June%2024%20to%20July%2013.%20Thirty-four%20deaths%20were%20due%20to%20landslides%2C%20cloudbursts%20and%20flash%20floods.%20Apart%20from%20fatalities%20and%20property%20damage%2C%20the%20rain%20fury%20brought%20lives%20to%20a%20standstill%20with%20more%20than%201%2C000%20roads%2C%20damaged%20bridges%2C%20power%20and%20water%20supply%20lines%20shutting%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20repeatedly%20warned%20about%20increasing%20incidents%20of%20cloudbursts%20due%20to%20climate%20change%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20other%20Himalayan%20states%20like%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20Uttarakhand.%20Shimla%20falls%20in%20the%20seismic%20zone%20IV%20(high%20damage%20risk%20zone)%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20and%20as%20far%20as%20landslide%20hazard%20is%20concerned%2C%2051%25%20of%20the%20area%20is%20in%20moderate%20and%2033%25%20cent%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20hazard%26quot%3B%20zone.%20Given%20the%20risk%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%205%2C000%20to%20over%2020%2C000%20people%20might%20die%20in%20the%20city%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20significant%20earthquake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnplanned%20and%20haphazard%20development%20increases%20people's%20susceptibility%20to%20natural%20disasters%20by%20increasing%20their%20physical%20exposure.%20The%20green%20tribunal%20had%20barred%20any%20construction%20activity%20in%20the%20core%20and%20green%20areas%20but%20the%20new%20draft%20SDP%20permits%20construction%20in%20these%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20obvious%20flaw%20is%20in%20the%20projected%20total%20population%20of%206.25%20lakh%20-%20both%20resident%20and%20floating%20-%20for%20the%20year%202041.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20kind%20of%20population%20projection%20is%20absurd.%20The%20growth%20rate%20of%20town%20in%20SDP%20has%20been%20calculated%20as%20400%25.%20That's%20ridiculous.%20No%20town%20grows%20400%25%20anywhere%20in%20India%20or%20world.%20Shimla%20is%2055%25%20forest.%20So%20where%20would%20people%20construct%20houses%3F%20The%20SDP%20doesn't%20talk%20of%20decongestion.%20The%20green%20zones%20that%20the%20SDP%20will%20allow%20construction%20in%20will%20only%20help%20powerful%20people%2C%20who%20have%20bought%20land%20in%20the%20green%20area.%20There%20is%20no%20talk%20of%20mobility%20in%20the%20SDP.%20We%20require%20suturing%20and%20acupuncture%20in%20the%20development%20plan%20in%20the%20form%20of%20redevelopment%2C%20retrofitting%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Panwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Shimla%20Development%20Plan%20must%20not%20be%20implemented%20in%20haste.%20Scientific%20and%20geological%20inputs%20should%20be%20given%20priority%20in%20the%20plan%20to%20ensure%20sustainable%20development%20of%20the%20city%20and%20the%20safety%20of%20its%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691398260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-02%2Fguuhg53g_shimla-summer-generic_625x300_18_February_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-a-plan-for-bursting-shimla-draws-huge-objections-4276055%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20population%20of%20Shimla%20is%20around%202.41%20lakh%2C%20as%20of%20Census%202011%2C%20besides%20a%20floating%20population%20of%20some%2070%2C000%20tourists%20per%20day%20during%20peak%20season.%20The%20hill%20station%20lacks%20a%20public%20transport%20system%2C%20parking%20space%20and%20pedestrian%20infrastructure.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-a-plan-for-bursting-shimla-draws-huge-objections-4276055%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-a-plan-for-bursting-shimla-draws-huge-objections-4276055%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-a-plan-for-bursting-shimla-draws-huge-objections-4276055%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Video%3A%20Fan%20forcibly%20hugs%20Park%20Seo-joon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691398138000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102497527%2Cimgsize-29726.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Ffan-forcibly-hugs-park-seo-joon-netizen-calls-it-sexual-harassment-watch-video%2Farticleshow%2F102497006.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102497006.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAfter%20winning%20hearts%20for%20his%20performance%20in%20'Dream'%2C%20Park%20Seo-joon%20will%20soon%20be%20seen%20in%20action%20packed%20thriller%20'Concrete%20Utopia'.%20At%20a%20promotional%20event%20for%20the%20movie%2C%20a%20fan%20was%20seen%20forcibly%20hugging%20the%20actor%20on%20the%20stage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Ffan-forcibly-hugs-park-seo-joon-netizen-calls-it-sexual-harassment-watch-video%2Farticleshow%2F102497006.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20rejects%20Go%20First%20plea%20against%20Delhi%20HC%20nod%20to%20lessors%20to%20access%20planes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691397644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-05%2F04%2Ffull%2F1683222810-491.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20August%203%2C%20the%20airline%20had%20moved%20to%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Delhi%20HC's%20order%20to%20allow%20lessors%20to%20inspect%20the%20aircraft%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Could%20Have%20Adverse%20Impact%20on%20Press%20Freedom%3A%20Editors%20Guild%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F06140651%2FIMG_6391-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20on%20Sunday%2C%20August%206%2C%20expressed%20a%20series%20of%20concerns%20it%20has%20over%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20saying%20it%20carries%20various%20provisions%20that%20can%20have%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20press%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Bill%20could%20be%20used%20to%C2%A0widen%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20existing%20powers%20of%20censorship%20because%20Clause%2037(1)(b)%20will%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccensor%20content%20on%20vague%20and%20unspecified%20grounds%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20general%20public'%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%20from%20certain%20obligations%20of%20the%20law%2C%20where%20the%20reporting%20on%20certain%20entities%20in%20public%20interest%20may%20conflict%20with%20their%20right%20to%20personal%20data%20protection.%20The%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20report%20had%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%98If%20journalists%20were%20made%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20grounds%20of%20processing%20personal%20data%2C%20it%20would%20be%20extremely%20onerous%20for%20them%20to%20access%20information%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%98mandating%20grounds%20of%20processing%20like%20consent%20would%20mean%20that%20accounts%20that%20are%20unfavourable%20to%20the%20data%20principal%20would%20simply%20not%20get%20published%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EGI%20also%20raised%20concerns%20that%20the%20Bull%20could%20%E2%80%9Cunreasonably%20widen%20the%20scope%20of%20exemptions%E2%80%9D%20available%20to%20public%20information%20officers%20of%20government%20ministries%20and%20departments%20to%20reject%20RTI%20applications%20on%20the%20simple%20basis%20that%20the%20information%20sought%20%E2%80%98relates%20to%20personal%20information%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20exemptions%20provided%20to%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20are%20near-absolute%2C%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20%5BDPB%5D%20to%20be%20constituted%20thereunder%20has%20not%20been%20provided%20sufficient%20independence%20and%20rulemaking%20powers%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20adds%2C%20noting%20that%20because%20that%20all%20members%20of%20the%20DPB%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20its%20%E2%80%9Cindependence%20remains%20in%20doubt%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20statement%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20has%20been%20presented%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20August%203%2C%202023%20by%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Union%20Minister%20for%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%2C%20Mr.%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw.%20The%20bill%20carries%20various%20provisions%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthat%20can%20have%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20press%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20highlight%20some%20of%20the%20primary%20concerns%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EA.%20Concerns%20over%20democratic%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20note%20the%20irregularities%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20brought%20before%20the%20Parliament.%20Bypassing%20democratic%20processes%2C%20such%20as%20transparency%20in%20the%20public%20consultation%20process%20as%20well%20as%20lapses%20in%20parliamentary%20procedure%20in%20tabling%20the%20Bill%20before%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20have%20contributed%20to%20the%20drafting%20of%20a%20Bill%20that%20provides%20significantly%20lower%20protections%20than%20those%20envisaged%20initially%20by%20the%20Justice%20BN%20Srikrishna%20Expert%20Committee%20and%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20landmark%20Privacy%20Judgment%20of%20Justice%20K.S.%20Puttaswamy%20v.%20Union%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EB.%20Concerns%20over%20surveillance%20over%20censorship%20and%20lack%20of%20surveillance%20reform%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20note%2C%20with%20dismay%2C%20that%20while%20the%20Bill%2C%20ostensibly%20to%20promote%20data%20protection%2C%20has%20failed%20to%20make%20any%20provisions%20that%20bring%20about%20the%20surveillance%20reform%20that%20is%20urgently%20needed%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20creates%20an%20enabling%20framework%20for%20surveillance%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%20While%20clause%2017(2)(a)%20allows%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20issue%20a%20notification%20exempting%20any%20%E2%80%9Cinstrumentality%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Bill%2C%20thereby%20out%20of%20the%20ambit%20of%20data%20protection%20restrictions%2C%20including%20internal%20sharing%20and%20processing%20of%20data%2C%20Section%2017(4)%20allows%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20to%20retain%20personal%20data%20for%20an%20unlimited%20period%20of%20time.%20Additionally%2C%20under%20Section%2036%2C%20the%20Government%20can%20ask%20any%20public%20or%20private%20entity%20(Data%20Fiduciary)%20to%20furnish%20personal%20information%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EC.%20Concerns%20over%20widening%20of%20censorship%20powers%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Bill%20provides%20the%20Union%20Government%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20widen%20its%20existing%20powers%20of%20censorship.%20Clause%2037(1)(b)%20of%20the%20Bill%20will%20allow%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20censor%20content%20on%20vague%20and%20unspecified%20grounds%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20general%20public%E2%80%99.%20This%20will%20increase%20censorship%20powers%20well%20beyond%20what%20is%20presently%20provided%20for%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20and%20may%20even%20be%20unconstitutional%20for%20going%20beyond%20the%20reasonable%20restrictions%20on%20free%20expression%20enumerated%20under%20Article%2019(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ED.%20Concerns%20over%20lack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalistic%20activities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%20from%20certain%20obligations%20of%20the%20law%2C%20where%20the%20reporting%20on%20certain%20entities%20in%20public%20interest%20may%20conflict%20with%20their%20right%20to%20personal%20data%20protection.%20The%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20report%20had%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9CIf%20journalists%20were%20made%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20grounds%20of%20processing%20personal%20data%2C%20it%20would%20be%20extremely%20onerous%20for%20them%20to%20access%20information%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmandating%20grounds%20of%20processing%20like%20consent%20would%20mean%20that%20accounts%20that%20are%20unfavourable%20to%20the%20data%20principal%20would%20simply%20not%20get%20published.%E2%80%9D%20It%20had%20thus%20provided%20a%20framework%20for%20balance%20between%20personal%20data%20protection%20and%20public%20interest%2C%20which%20we%20note%20is%20missing%20from%20the%20current%20bill.%20This%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20journalistic%20activity%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EE.%20Concern%20over%20impact%20on%20the%20Right%20To%20Information%20(RTI)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20has%20been%20already%20been%20pointed%20out%20by%20some%20activists%2C%20certain%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20Clause%2044(3)%20for%20instance%2C%20unreasonably%20widen%20the%20scope%20of%20exemptions%20available%20to%20Public%20Information%20Officers%20of%20government%20ministries%20and%20departments%20to%20reject%20RTI%20applications%20under%20Section%208(1)(i)%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20on%20the%20simple%20basis%20that%20the%20information%20sought%20%E2%80%98relates%20to%20personal%20information%E2%80%99.%20The%20RTI%20Act%20in%20its%20present%20form%20strikes%20a%20balance%20between%20privacy%20and%20the%20right%20to%20public%20information.%20This%20provision%20shifts%20the%20balance%20in%20favour%20of%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%2C%20including%20information%20which%20is%20being%20sought%20by%20journalists%20in%20public%20interest%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20accountability.%20It%20is%20necessary%20that%20the%20RTI%20Act%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3Enot%20be%20weakened.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EF.%20Concerns%20over%20the%20composition%20of%20and%20appointment%20to%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhile%20exemptions%20provided%20to%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20are%20near-absolute%2C%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20to%20be%20constituted%20thereunder%20has%20not%20been%20provided%20sufficient%20independence%20and%20rulemaking%20powers.%20Lawyers%2C%20scholars%20and%20even%20judgments%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20have%20noted%20that%20Tribunals%20(such%20as%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board)%20must%20remain%20independent%20of%20control%20by%20the%20executive%2C%20to%20maintain%20their%20effectiveness%20and%20credibility.%20However%2C%20given%20that%20all%20members%20of%20the%20DPB%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20Union%20Government%20(Clause%2019(2))%2C%20its%20independence%20remains%20in%20doubt.%20Considering%20the%20huge%20fines%20that%20can%20potentially%20be%20imposed%2C%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Board%20from%20executive%20interference%20is%20vital%20to%20preserve%20liberty.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Guild%20urges%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20to%20reconsider%20the%20provisions%20that%20Editor%E2%80%99s%20Guild%20of%20India%20has%20highlighted%2C%20and%20work%20to%20offer%20a%20data%20protection%20legislation%20to%20Indian%20citizens%20that%20does%20not%20compromise%20their%20right%20to%20free%20expression%2C%20right%20to%20information%20and%20right%20to%20a%20free%20press.%20Further%2C%20the%20Guild%20urges%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20to%20place%20the%20Bill%20before%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20for%20deliberation%20on%20the%20issues%20raised%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20reconsider%20those%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Guild%20has%20already%20written%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20leaders%20of%20political%20parties%20in%20both%20the%20houses%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Minister%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%2C%20highlighting%20our%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691396956000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F06140651%2FIMG_6391-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-bill-adverse-impact-press-freedom-editors-guild%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Guild%20pointed%20out%20several%20concerns%20it%20has%20over%20provision%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20of%20wider%20censorship%20powers%2C%20surveillance%20and%20reducing%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-bill-adverse-impact-press-freedom-editors-guild%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Railway%20Cop%20Who%20Killed%204%20On%20Moving%20Train%20Charged%20With%20%5C%22Promoting%20Enmity%5C%22%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20week%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frailway-cop-sent-for-mental-health-check-over-killings-no-communal-angle-4259764%5C%22%3Erefuting%20any%20communal%20link%20in%20the%20shocking%20murder%20of%20four%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20Railway%20Protection%20Force%20(RPF)%20constable%20aboard%20a%20Jaipur-Mumbai%20train%2C%20the%20railway%20police%20has%20added%20sections%20of%20the%20law%20relating%20to%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%20to%20the%20case%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20Railway%20Police%20(GRP)%2C%20in%20the%20First%20Information%20Report%2C%20or%20FIR%2C%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffour-passengers-on-jaipur-mumbai-train-shot-dead-by-railway-protection-force-constable-4254266%5C%22%3Eaccused%20RPF%20Constable%20Chetan%20Singh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20added%20Section%20153A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20which%20relate%20to%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%2C%20race%2C%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20residence%2C%20language%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20informed%20the%20court%20today%20during%20the%20accused's%20remand.%20The%20court%20has%20granted%20police%20custody%20of%20the%20accused%20till%20August%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FIR%20also%20includes%20IPC%20Section%20302%20(murder)%2C%20Arms%20Act%203%2C%2025%2C%2027%2C%20and%20Railways%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20video%20of%20Chetan%20Singh%20on%20the%20train%2C%20seemingly%20recorded%20by%20passengers%2C%20showing%20a%20bloody%20body%20of%20a%20man%20who%20was%20shot%20lying%20at%20his%20feet%20while%20he%20made%20a%20communal%20speech%20mentioning%20Pakistan%20and%20domestic%20political%20issues%2C%20had%20gone%20viral%20soon%20after%20the%20horrific%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%2C%20which%20NDTV%20can't%20independently%20verify%2C%20the%20accused%20went%20on%20a%20tirade%20mentioning%20Pakistan%2C%20Indian%20media%2C%20and%20mentioned%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%20Yogi%20Adityanath%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BThackeray%26quot%3B.%20Officials%20haven't%20so%20far%20denied%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...%3Cem%3EAgar%20vote%20dena%20hai%2C%20agar%20Hindustan%20me%20rehna%20hai%2C%20toh%20mai%20kehta%20hoon%2C%20Modi%20aur%20Yogi%2C%20ye%20do%20hain%2C%20aur%20aapke%20Thackeray%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(...If%20you%20want%20to%20vote%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20live%20in%20India%2C%20then%20I%20say%2C%20Modi%20and%20Yogi%2C%20these%20are%20the%20two%2C%20and%20your%20Thackeray')%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20can%20be%20heard%20saying%20in%20the%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20of%20the%20people%20Chetan%20Singh%20shot%20dead%20were%20Muslims.%20The%20accused%20first%20shot%20his%20superior%2C%20Sub-Inspector%20Tika%20Ram%20Meena%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fjaipur-mumbai-superfast-express-rpf-railway-protection-force-mumbai-train-shooting-chetan-singh-what-led-to-railway-cop-shooting-4-dead-on-train-his-c-4257606%5C%22%3Ewent%20from%20coach%20to%20coach%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20which%20he%20killed%20three%20passengers%20--%20Abdul%20Qadirbhai%20Mohammed%20Hussain%20Bhanpurwala%2C%20Akhtar%20Abbas%20Ali%2C%20and%20Sadar%20Mohammed%20Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20was%20sent%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bmental%20health%20assessment%26q