il-gaya-climax%2Farticleshow%2F102494570.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parliamentary%20Panel%20Cautions%20EC%20Against%20Rushing%20to%20Prepare%20Common%20Electoral%20Roll%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F10111348%2FEC.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20has%20cautioned%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(EC)%20against%20rushing%20to%20prepare%20a%20common%20electoral%20roll%20without%20looking%20into%20the%20Constitutional%20provisions%20and%20powers%20of%20states%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Findia%2Felection-commission-should-keep-in-mind-principles-of-federalism-says-parliamentary-standing-committee-2636872%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20EC%20should%20adhere%20to%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%9Cfederalism%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccarefully%20assess%20potential%20consequences%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20present%2C%20the%20EC%20prepares%20the%20voter%E2%80%99s%20list%20for%20Parliament%20and%20Assembly%20polls%20while%20for%20local%20body%20polls%2C%20the%20electoral%20roll%20is%20prepared%20by%20the%20State%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20suggested%20that%20the%20EC%20should%20hold%20extensive%20consultations%20with%20the%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20law%20department%2C%20state%20governments%20and%20parties%20while%20expressing%20concerns%20about%20the%20potential%20impact%20of%20a%20common%20roll%20on%20the%20constitutional%20powers%20of%20the%20states%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ECI%20may%20also%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20principles%20of%20federalism%20enshrined%20under%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20powers%20reserved%20for%20the%20State%20Election%20Commissions%20under%20List%20II%20Entry%205%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20%E2%80%98Specific%20Aspects%20of%20Election%20Process%20and%20Their%20Reform%E2%80%99%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20common%20electoral%20roll%20%E2%80%93%20a%20suggestion%20which%20was%20first%20made%20in%201999%20by%20the%20then%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20through%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20as%20it%20believes%20it%20would%20reduce%20the%20cost%20and%20efforts%20involved%20in%20the%20process%20of%20preparing%20separate%20lists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20the%20committee%20has%20taken%20note%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpotential%20benefits%E2%80%9D%20of%20a%20common%20electoral%20roll%20but%20it%20stressed%20the%20importance%20of%20proper%20constitutional%20and%20statutory%20authorisation%20before%20the%20EC%20takes%20charge%20of%20creating%20electoral%20rolls%20for%20State%20Election%20Commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20cautioned%20the%20EC%20against%20treating%20all%20regions%20in%20India%20as%20identical%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20further%20observed%20that%20implementing%20the%20common%20roll%20is%20currently%20outside%20the%20scope%20of%20Article%20325%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20%3Cem%3EThePrint%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fgovernance%2Fhouse-panel-cautions-modi-govt-on-proposed-common-voter-list-avoid-stepping-into-states-domain%2F1700380%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Article%20stipulates%20that%20separate%20electoral%20rolls%20must%20be%20used%20for%20elections%20to%20Parliament%20and%20the%20state%20legislatures.%20The%20panel%20suggested%20that%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20actions%20are%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Constitution%2C%20%E2%80%9Cconsensus%20shall%20be%20m