%20And%20then%20remember%20that%20%3Ci%3Ethey%3C%2Fi%3E%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20define%20what%20India%20is%20%E2%80%93%20or%20to%20determine%20how%20Indians%20should%20live%20and%20relate%20to%20each%20other.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Chishti%20on%20stage%2C%20Prakash%20Raj%20referred%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20Manipur%2C%20where%20more%20than%20150%20persons%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20women%20raped%20and%20thousands%20displaced%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Haryana.%20He%20said%20fraternity%20means%20to%20care%20and%20to%20love%20but%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20as%20a%20society%20have%20lost%20this%20and%20we%20the%20country%20and%20citizens%20have%20to%20understand%20this%20reality.%E2%80%9D%20The%20fact%20is%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Csomebody%E2%80%99s%20pain%20does%20not%20become%20our%20pain%20anymore.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20France%20where%20there%20was%20widespread%20public%20revulsion%20over%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fjun%2F27%2Fpolice-officer-investigated-boy-shot-dead-paris-nanterre%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20police%20shooting%20of%20a%2017-year-old%20boy%2C%20Nael%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20France%20because%20a%20boy%20is%20shot%20dead%2C%20a%20country%20rises%2C%20because%20there%20is%20Fraternity.%20But%20not%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%20Reaching%20into%20the%20epics%2C%20Raj%20sought%20to%20illustrate%20the%20essence%20of%20fraternity%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20cut%20your%20finger%3B%20you%20feel%20the%20pain.%20Eklavya%20cuts%20his%20finger%3B%20we%20all%20feel%20the%20pain.%20That%20is%20fraternity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEklavya%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98low%20caste%E2%80%99%20warrior%20and%20archer%20of%20great%20accomplishment%20whose%20caste%20Hindu%20teacher%20insisted%20he%20cut%20off%20his%20right%20thumb%20as%20payment%20for%20the%20lessons%20he%20had%20taught.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChishti%20asked%20the%20actor%20about%20how%20the%20film%20industry%20was%20being%20affected%20by%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98We%20have%20gone%20from%20%3Cem%3EAmar%20Akbar%20Antony%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20%3Cem%3EKerala%20Story%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98-like%20hate%20films%20which%20were%20undermining%20fraternity%20in%20India.%20Raj%20said%20that%20the%20situation%20was%20made%20worse%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20was%20becoming%20harder%20for%20others%20to%20make%20films%20that%20do%20not%20toe%20a%20particular%20line.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20reached%20a%20situation%20where%20filmmakers%20are%20worried%20their%20films%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20made%20or%20shown%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07113132%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-07-at-11.00.12-AM-2.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07113132%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-07-at-11.00.12-AM-2.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07113132%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-07-at-11.00.12-AM-2-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07113132%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-07-at-11.00.12-AM-2-1024x576.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666945%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESeema%20Chishti%20and%20Prakash%20Raj%20at%20The%20Wire%20Dialogues.%20Photo%3A%20Devi%20Dutt%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20part%20of%20a%20wider%20culture%20of%20fear%20across%20the%20country.%20%E2%80%9CFear%20has%20become%20a%20national%20disease%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9C%5BPeople%5D%20whisper%2C%E2%80%9D%20when%20they%20are%20being%20critical.%20%E2%80%9CI%20know%20I%20take%20risks%20when%20I%20speak%2C%20and%20with%20my%20theatre%20project%20%E2%80%93%20Nirdigantha%20%E2%80%93%20but%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20let%20people%20down.%E2%80%9D%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Fprakash-raj-to-open-institution-for-performing-arts-in-mysuru-1178852.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaj%20announced%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Nirdigantha%20%E2%80%93%20or%20%E2%80%98endless%20horizons%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20a%20theatre%20venture%20he%20will%20incubate%20in%20Mysore%20which%20will%20produce%2020%20plays%20and%20take%20them%20on%20tour%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaj%20blamed%20politicians%20for%20fostering%20divisions%20and%20inequality.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20dig%20a%20mosque%2C%20you%20will%20find%20a%20temple.%20If%20you%20dig%20a%20temple%2C%20you%20will%20find%20a%20Buddhist%20structure.%20How%20long%20are%20you%20going%20to%20keep%20digging%3F%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20asked.%20%E2%80%9CToday%20more%20than%20religion%20and%20caste%20it%20is%20money%20power%20that%20is%20driving%20politics%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20but%20this%20was%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20money%20and%20we%20normally%20forget%20that.%20%E2%80%9CPoliticians%20come%20once%20in%20five%20years%20and%20go.%20We%20are%20permanent.%20Politics%20is%20us.%20It%20is%20our%20money.%20He%20flies%2C%20eats%20mushrooms%2C%20acts%20like%20a%20stationmaster.%20But%20it%20is%20our%20money.%E2%80%9D%20He%20called%20the%20rulers%20rakshasas%2C%20or%20demons%2C%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20these%20%3Cspan%3Erakshasas%3C%2Fspan%3E%20are%20desperate%2C%20there%20is%20no%20telling%20what%20they%20will%20do.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReminded%20by%20Chishti%20of%20what%20he%20had%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20last%20year%20%E2%80%93%20that%20we%20are%20partying%20on%20a%20sinking%20ship%E2%80%A6%20the%20economy%2C%20prosperity%20etc%20is%20all%20sinking%20%E2%80%93%20Raj%20said%20that%20this%20was%20indeed%20the%20situation%20today.%20%E2%80%9CI%20want%20to%20ask%20those%20who%20speak%20of%20making%20India%20the%20Number%20One%20Economy%3A%20Where%20is%20Fraternity%20in%20your%20economy%3F%20Why%20is%20the%20one%20percent%20so%20far%20ahead%20of%20the%2099%25%3F%E2%80%9D.%20This%20was%20why%20the%20ship%20was%20sinking%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20person%20promising%20to%20make%20India%20number%20one%20will%20be%20sure%20to%20get%20away%20but%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20will%20go%20down%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Seema%20Chishti%20asked%20him%20what%20gives%20him%20hope%2C%20the%20actor%20said%20young%20people%20did.%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CYoungsters%20do.%20Their%20energy.%20Their%20sense%20of%20dignity%E2%80%A6%20I%20have%20seen%20young%20people%20at%20Seed%20Festivals%20in%20Karnataka.%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20young%20people%20like%20Mohammed%20Zubair%20(a%20founder%20of%20AltNews)%2C%20the%20jailed%20activist%20Umar%20Khalid%20and%20the%20stand-up%20comic%20Kunal%20Kamra%20gave%20him%20hope.%20Above%20all%2C%20he%20said%2C%20people%20had%20to%20believe%20in%20their%20own%20strength.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShabnam%20Virmani%2C%20of%20the%20Kabir%20Project%20%E2%80%93%20which%20attempts%20to%20take%20a%20comprehensive%20look%20at%20Kabir%E2%80%99s%20thoughts%20and%20poetry%20%E2%80%93%20kick-started%20the%20conversation%20on%20fraternity%2C%20through%20music%20and%20verse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20sang%20folk%20songs%20of%20Kabir%2C%20she%20struck%20the%20perfect%20note%20as%20a%20prelude%20to%20the%20discussion%20with%20Prakash%20Raj%20which%20followed.%20Virmani%2C%20whose%20work%20on%20Kabir%20is%20arguably%20the%20most%20multi-faceted%20in%20recent%20times%2C%20combining%20scholarship%2C%20art%20and%20performance%2C%20pointed%20to%20the%20poet-saint%E2%8